For completeness and recall information that is text-extracted, a reasonable baseline is to consider the extraction time as the latest validity time. Finer-grained annotations are possible, for instance, by considering document creation time metadata, or temporal expressions in the actual text, for estimating the latest (certain) validity time [heideltime].